        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 4:13PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 413 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from near Hytop to Pisgah to near Hammondville to near
Cornwall Furnace Park to near Ball Flat, and moving northeast at 40
mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Rome, Lafayette, Summerville, Trenton, Trion, Cave Spring, La
Fayette, Lyerly, Menlo, Center Post, Subligna, Linwood, Coosa,
Cloudland, Cooper Heights, Cloudland Canyon State Park, James H.
Floyd State Park, Holland, Naomi, and Rising Fawn.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
